#Sen Triplets (#1085): at my upkeep, I may cast cards from the opponent's hand
#this turn. Cross to my turn-3 upkeep, accept the may, tap myrs, cast their
#grizzly bears -> bears enter MY battlefield.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:sen triplets,copper myr,leaden myr
[PLAYER2]
hand:grizzly bears
library:millstone,millstone
[DO]
goto end
goto upkeep
goto end
goto upkeep
copper myr
leaden myr
goto upkeep
choice 0
goto upkeep
grizzly bears
goto upkeep
choice 0
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
[ASSERT]
UPKEEP
[PLAYER1]
inplay:sen triplets,copper myr,leaden myr,grizzly bears
tappedinplay:2
[PLAYER2]
hand:millstone
library:millstone
[END]
#PARKED after 5 iterations: the upkeep trigger fires and resolves (StackAbility
#in log) but the "may castcard(normal) target(*|opponenthand)" leg produces NO
#interaction whatsoever - no may-menu, no target chooser, log silent after
#resolution. Tried: choice-0-then-click, taps-before-choice, pads between every
#step, trailing cast-mode choice 0. Myr taps work (mana floats), bears click is
#found-but-inert. AACastCard uses the isReactingToTargetClick protocol and never
#became reactive -> the may/castcard leg of a triggered && chain never spawns.
#Related untested idiom users: the Expertise cycle (spell-context may castcard),
#Mind's Dilation, Leaf-Crowned Elder (kinship+reveal). Engine-round fuel:
#trigger-context gaps family (queue item 2) or a castcard-specific resolution gap.
#Other legs (noactivatedability / maxCast(*)0 lockout) untested in this probe.
